The paper discusses a methodology for verifying the security properties of network protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of formal methods for verification, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the iterative nature of the methodology, which is related to the topic of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
